<!-- PAGE HEADER -->
<div class="page-header fu1">
  <p class="eyebrow">Our Purpose</p>
  <h1 class="page-title">Understanding yourself. <em>Understanding each other.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Good intentions aren't enough on their own. The couples who thrive aren't the ones who never struggle — they're the ones who actually understand how the other person is wired. That's what Attune is for.</p>
</div>

<!-- RESEARCH -->
<div class="research-section">
  <div class="si">
    <p class="s-eye">Grounded in research</p>
    <h2 class="s-title">This isn't intuition. It's evidence.</h2>
    <p class="s-sub">The exercises behind Attune are informed by decades of relationship science, not pop psychology. Here's what the research says about why structured understanding matters.</p>
    <div class="research-grid">
      <div class="research-card rc-orange">
        <div class="research-label">Expectations &amp; satisfaction</div>
        <p class="research-body">Couples who discuss expectations early in the relationship report significantly higher relationship satisfaction, even years later. The conversations that feel premature are often the most valuable.</p>
        <p class="research-src">Gottman, J.M. & Silver, N. — The Seven Principles for Making Marriage Work</p>
      </div>
      <div class="research-card rc-blue">
        <div class="research-label">Unspoken assumptions</div>
        <p class="research-body">A substantial portion of relationship dissatisfaction traces back not to incompatibility, but to unexamined assumptions about roles, finances, and communication styles. Most couples only discover the gap when it becomes a problem.</p>
        <p class="research-src">Markman, H.J., Stanley, S.M., & Blumberg, S.L. — Fighting for Your Marriage</p>
      </div>
      <div class="research-card rc-green">
        <div class="research-label">Mutual understanding</div>
        <p class="research-body">Self-disclosure and partner understanding are among the strongest predictors of long-term relationship quality. Being genuinely known, and knowing your partner, is foundational, not supplementary.</p>
        <p class="research-src">Reis, H.T. &amp; Shaver, P. — Intimacy as an Interpersonal Process (1988)</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Methodology reference -->
    <div style="margin-top:2.5rem;padding-top:2rem;border-top:1px solid var(--stone);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;">
      <div>
        <p style="font-size:.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--clay);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;margin-bottom:.35rem;">For the curious</p>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 .5rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;max-width:480px;">The full research basis for each of Attune's 10 communication dimensions, the 6-axis classification system, and the derivation methodology are documented for review.</p>
        <a href="/how-it-works" style="font-size:.8rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--orange);text-decoration:none;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.3rem;" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">
          See how it works →
        </a>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:.65rem;flex-wrap:wrap;flex-shrink:0;">
        <a href="/attune-methodology.docx" download style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.45rem;background:var(--warm);border:1.5px solid var(--stone);border-radius:9px;padding:.55rem 1.1rem;font-size:.78rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--clay);text-decoration:none;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;transition:all .15s;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='var(--clay)'" onmouseout="this.style.borderColor='var(--stone)'">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
          Methodology
        </a>
        <a href="/attune-couple-type-overview.docx" download style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.45rem;background:var(--warm);border:1.5px solid var(--stone);border-radius:9px;padding:.55rem 1.1rem;font-size:.78rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--clay);text-decoration:none;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;transition:all .15s;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='var(--clay)'" onmouseout="this.style.borderColor='var(--stone)'">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
          Type classification
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- PRINCIPLES -->
<div class="principles">
  <div class="si">
    <p class="s-eye">How we think about this</p>
    <h2 class="s-title">How we think about it.</h2>
    <p class="s-sub">Understanding how your partner is wired isn't about changing them. It's about meeting them where they actually are, and building from there. Three principles behind everything we build.</p>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;margin-top:3rem;">
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:80px 1fr;gap:2rem;align-items:start;padding:2rem 0;border-top:1px solid var(--stone);">
        <div style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif;font-size:3.5rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(193,127,71,.18);line-height:1;letter-spacing:-.03em;">01</div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:.6rem;">Your answers, not ours</h3>
          <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.78;font-weight:300;max-width:560px;">Attune doesn't tell you who you are as a couple. It helps you see yourselves, from your own responses, side by side. The insight is always yours. We provide the framework; the meaning comes entirely from what you each bring to it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:80px 1fr;gap:2rem;align-items:start;padding:2rem 0;border-top:1px solid var(--stone);">
        <div style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif;font-size:3.5rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(193,127,71,.18);line-height:1;letter-spacing:-.03em;">02</div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:.6rem;">Clarity before conflict</h3>
          <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.78;font-weight:300;max-width:560px;">Assumptions about roles, finances, communication, and values quietly shape relationships long before they surface as friction. The conversations that feel premature are often the most valuable. Naming them early, while they're still easy, changes everything.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:80px 1fr;gap:2rem;align-items:start;padding:2rem 0;border-top:1px solid var(--stone);border-bottom:1px solid var(--stone);">
        <div style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif;font-size:3.5rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(193,127,71,.18);line-height:1;letter-spacing:-.03em;">03</div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:.6rem;">Built for the long haul</h3>
          <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.78;font-weight:300;max-width:560px;">Understanding isn't a one-time event. What each of you needs and envisions will evolve, sometimes slowly, sometimes suddenly. Attune is designed to be revisited: not just a starting point, but an ongoing reference for the relationship you're building.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- COUPLE TYPING CALLOUT -->
<section style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e1a48,#2e2a68);padding:5rem 2.5rem;">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:960px;">
    <div class="couple-typing-grid" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:4rem;align-items:center;">
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',Georgia,serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,2.6rem);font-weight:700;color:white;line-height:1.05;margin-bottom:1rem;letter-spacing:-.02em;">What makes Attune different: a typing system built for couples, not individuals.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:.92rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,.72);line-height:1.82;font-weight:300;margin-bottom:1.25rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Most personality tools tell you about yourself. Attune tells you about <em style="font-style:italic;color:rgba(255,255,255,.88);">you two together</em>. The couple type isn't derived from either person's answers alone — it emerges from the combination. Your 50-question individual profile places you on two behavioral axes. Your partner's answers do the same. The pairing of where you each land is what generates the couple type.</p>
        <p style="font-size:.92rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,.72);line-height:1.82;font-weight:300;margin-bottom:2rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">The result is a visual map — two dots on a grid — showing where each of you sits across the dimensions that most shape how you grow together: how you respond when tension arrives, and how freely your interior life surfaces into the relationship. The distance between your dots, the quadrants you occupy, and your proximity to the lines between them all carry meaning.</p>
        <a href="/how-it-works#couple-typing" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;background:rgba(232,103,58,1);color:white;padding:.75rem 1.5rem;border-radius:10px;font-size:.78rem;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase;">How the typing works →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="couple-typing-map">
        <!-- 2x2 map illustration -->
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,.06);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);border-radius:18px;padding:1.5rem;position:relative;">
          <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2px;aspect-ratio:1;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.15);border-radius:8px;overflow:hidden;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
            <!-- X: top-left -->
            <div style="background:rgba(27,95,232,.18);display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:flex-start;padding:.65rem;font-size:.58rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(27,95,232,.6);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">X — The Driver</div>
            <!-- W: top-right -->
            <div style="background:rgba(232,103,58,.15);display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:flex-end;padding:.65rem;font-size:.58rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(232,103,58,.7);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;text-align:right;">W — The Reacher</div>
            <!-- Z: bottom-left -->
            <div style="background:rgba(107,114,128,.12);display:flex;align-items:flex-end;justify-content:flex-start;padding:.65rem;font-size:.58rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(107,114,128,.65);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Z — The Undercurrent</div>
            <!-- Y: bottom-right -->
            <div style="background:rgba(124,58,237,.15);display:flex;align-items:flex-end;justify-content:flex-end;padding:.65rem;font-size:.58rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(124,58,237,.65);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;text-align:right;">Y — The Feeler</div>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.5rem;">
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.65rem;">
              <div style="width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:#E8673A;flex-shrink:0;box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(232,103,58,.2);"></div>
              <span style="font-size:.72rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,.65);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Partner 1 — Type W, Reacher</span>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.65rem;">
              <div style="width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:#1B5FE8;flex-shrink:0;box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(27,95,232,.2);"></div>
              <span style="font-size:.72rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,.65);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Partner 2 — Type X, Driver</span>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top:.25rem;padding:.65rem .85rem;background:rgba(232,103,58,.12);border:1px solid rgba(232,103,58,.25);border-radius:8px;">
              <span style="font-size:.68rem;font-weight:700;color:rgba(232,103,58,.9);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">The Common Goal</span>
              <p style="font-size:.62rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;margin:.15rem 0 0;line-height:1.5;">Both want resolution. Different instruments, same direction.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

